{"data":[{"type":"questionAttempts","id":"17617692","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionAttempts/17617692"},"attributes":{"position":0,"marks":1,"score":1,"answeredAt":"2025-09-30T15:15:31+09:30","options":[1],"response":null,"finalizedAt":"2025-09-30T15:15:31+09:30"},"relationships":{"user":{"data":{"type":"users","id":"50098"}},"questionSession":{"data":null},"session":{"data":null},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16478"}},"bookmark":{"data":null}}}],"included":[{"type":"questions","id":"16478","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questions/16478"},"attributes":{"optionProportions":[0.3,0.48,0.04,0.11,0.07]},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9169"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74987"}}}},{"type":"items","id":"9169","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/items/9169"},"attributes":{"contentType":"question"},"relationships":{"content":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16478"}},"activeRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60493"}},"tags":{"data":[{"type":"tags","id":"7"},{"type":"tags","id":"31"},{"type":"tags","id":"67"},{"type":"tags","id":"71"},{"type":"tags","id":"74"},{"type":"tags","id":"2560"},{"type":"tags","id":"4930"},{"type":"tags","id":"4931"},{"type":"tags","id":"4937"},{"type":"tags","id":"4947"},{"type":"tags","id":"4950"},{"type":"tags","id":"5908"},{"type":"tags","id":"8512"},{"type":"tags","id":"11071"}]},"contributions":{"data":[{"type":"contributions","id":"21772"},{"type":"contributions","id":"21775"},{"type":"contributions","id":"25882"}]}},"meta":{"canRevise":false,"canManage":false,"canDelete":false}},{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74987","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/questionRevisions/74987"},"attributes":{"stem":"\u003Cp\u003ESmall cell lung cancer is associated with various paraneoplastic syndromes. One such syndrome presents with proximal muscle weakness that improves with exercise, reduced deep tendon reflexes, and autonomic symptoms such as dry mouth and constipation.\u003C/p\u003E","stemQuestion":"Which one of the following best describes this paraneoplastic syndrome?","responseType":"sba","marks":1,"options":["Guillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome","Lambert-Eaton myasthenic syndrome","Multiple sclerosis","Myasthenia gravis","Polymyositis"],"correctOptions":[1],"correctResponses":null,"explanation":"\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003ELambert-Eaton myasthenic syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is a paraneoplastic disorder where autoantibodies target voltage-gated calcium channels at presynaptic nerve terminals. This reduces acetylcholine release at the neuromuscular junction, causing characteristic weakness that improves with repeated muscle use.\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cp\u003EThe incorrect options can be explained:\u003C/p\u003E\u003Cul\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMyasthenia gravis\u003C/strong\u003E involves autoantibodies against postsynaptic acetylcholine receptors and typically worsens with exercise\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EGuillain-Barr\u00e9 syndrome\u003C/strong\u003E is an ascending paralysis that typically begins in the distal limbs\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EMultiple sclerosis\u003C/strong\u003E is a demyelinating disorder not typically associated with small cell lung cancer\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003Cli\u003E\u003Cp\u003E\u003Cstrong\u003EPolymyositis\u003C/strong\u003E is an inflammatory myopathy that does not show improvement with exercise\u003C/p\u003E\u003C/li\u003E\u003C/ul\u003E\u003Cp\u003ESmall cell lung cancer is found in approximately 60% of patients with Lambert-Eaton myasthenic syndrome, making it an important paraneoplastic association to recognise.\u003C/p\u003E","optionExplanations":["","","","",""],"learningPoints":["Lambert-Eaton myasthenic syndrome is a paraneoplastic disorder commonly associated with small cell lung cancer.","The condition is caused by autoantibodies against P/Q-type voltage-gated calcium channels at the presynaptic nerve terminal.","Characteristic symptoms include proximal muscle weakness, reduced reflexes, and autonomic dysfunction."],"references":["Kesner VG, Oh SJ, Dimachkie MM, Barohn RJ. Lambert-Eaton Myasthenic Syndrome. Neurol Clin. 2018 May;36(2):379-394. doi: 10.1016/j.ncl.2018.01.008. PMID: 29655456; PMCID: PMC6690495.","Gilhus NE. Lambert-eaton myasthenic syndrome; pathogenesis, diagnosis, and therapy. Autoimmune Dis. 2011;2011:973808. doi: 10.4061/2011/973808. Epub 2011 Sep 29. PMID: 21969911; PMCID: PMC3182560.","Jayarangaiah A, Lui F, Theetha Kariyanna P. Lambert-Eaton Myasthenic Syndrome. 2023 Oct 23. In: StatPearls [Internet]. Treasure Island (FL): StatPearls Publishing; 2024 Jan\u2013. PMID: 29939668.","Kumar, V., Abbas, A. K., \u0026 Aster, J. C. (Eds.). (2012). Robbins basic pathology e-book. Elsevier Health Science"]},"relationships":{"itemRevision":{"data":{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60493"}},"question":{"data":{"type":"questions","id":"16478"}},"stemMedia":{"data":[]},"explanationMedia":{"data":[]}}},{"type":"itemRevisions","id":"60493","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/itemRevisions/60493"},"attributes":{"createdAt":"2024-12-28T16:39:46+10:30","updatedAt":"2024-12-28T16:40:13+10:30"},"relationships":{"item":{"data":{"type":"items","id":"9169"}},"content":{"data":{"type":"questionRevisions","id":"74987"}}},"meta":{"canDelete":false}},{"type":"tags","id":"7","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/7"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83e\udde0","name":"Neurology","synonyms":[],"description":null,"position":null,"createdAt":null,"updatedAt":"2024-11-21T09:49:45+10:30"},"relationships":{"group":{"data":{"type":"tagGroups","id":"1"}},"heading":{"data":{"type":"tagHeadings","id":"1"}}},"meta":{"itemCount":0}},{"type":"tags","id":"31","links":{"self":"https://app.emedici.com/api/tags/31"},"attributes":{"emoji":"\ud83c\udf97","name":"Oncology","synonyms":[],"descri